185
00:08:57,780 --> 00:08:58,650
Of course we'd watch the Gala.

186
00:08:58,650 --> 00:08:59,740
Look. They're so happy.

187
00:09:00,400 --> 00:09:01,110
Indeed.

188
00:09:02,450 --> 00:09:04,320
Here. Try the tea I made.

189
00:09:04,450 --> 00:09:05,320
Thank you, grandpa.

190
00:09:09,950 --> 00:09:10,970
Is it good?

191
00:09:12,450 --> 00:09:13,610
It's really good.

192
00:09:13,900 --> 00:09:15,990
It tastes a little sweet.

193
00:09:16,450 --> 00:09:17,190
Yeah, you're right.

194
00:09:17,200 --> 00:09:19,490
There are rules when it comes to making tea.

195
00:09:19,740 --> 00:09:21,110
What rules?

196
00:09:21,150 --> 00:09:22,360
I don't understand.

197
00:09:23,400 --> 00:09:25,610
Have you heard of the Tea Sage?

198
00:09:26,360 --> 00:09:27,610
That's Lu Yu, right?

199
00:09:27,950 --> 00:09:28,490
Good.

200
00:09:28,990 --> 00:09:30,900
I know he once said that:

201
00:09:31,150 --> 00:09:34,030
"Mountain spring is the best, river water comes next,

202
00:09:34,110 --> 00:09:35,625
well water is the worst."

203
00:09:35,626 --> 00:09:36,320
Am I right?

204
00:09:36,320 --> 00:09:37,150
Yes, you're right.

205
00:09:37,190 --> 00:09:38,280
The choice of tea is important.

206
00:09:38,320 --> 00:09:39,780
Water also plays a major role.

207
00:09:40,900 --> 00:09:41,990
I get it.

208
00:09:43,450 --> 00:09:45,240
Good water makes good tea.

209
00:09:48,070 --> 00:09:49,530
Boss, you're back.

210
00:09:51,030 --> 00:09:51,860
Just finished running

211
00:09:51,900 --> 00:09:53,490
